<p id="Par22" class="p">In the solution of Eq. [
 <xref rid="Equ2" ref-type="" class="xref">2</xref>], after a sufficient long time, the term that describes the transient disturbance since 
 <italic class="italic">t</italic> = 0 becomes negligible (i.e., the effect of the initial temperature function is lost)
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR13" class="xref">13</xref>
 </sup>. Thus, the solution of Eq. [
 <xref rid="Equ2" ref-type="" class="xref">2</xref>] for the periodic steady-state is as follows
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR13" class="xref">13</xref>,
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR14" class="xref">14</xref>
 </sup>:
 <disp-formula id="Equ4" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">4</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
